 Port Elizabeth - Some welcome rains were recorded over the Eastern and Southern  Cape since Saturday - the latest rainfall figures show. According to the data from the Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service, while the rains are welcome, its a mixed bag at the catchment areas where the dams that supply the Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality and the Kouga Local Municipality are located. Residents are still urged to do everything they can to save water. Station Names 18 Jan 19 Jan 20 Jan 21 Jan 22 Jan Nelson Mandela Bay      AWOS Port Elizabeth Airport 2.2 2.6 1.6 0.2 7.8 ARS 3rd Ave Dip 2.6 4.0 1.0 NIL 24.2 ARS Blue Horizon Bay 7.6 3.2 1.0 * 15.0 ARS Chatty * 5.4 NIL 0.8 13.6 AWS Coega 5.2 0.8 NIL 0.2 3.2 AWSH Fettes Road 2.2 1.8 0.2 NIL 9.8 ARS Flower Reserve 11.4 * * NIL 4.2 AWSH Motherwell * * * * * ARS Riverstone Bridge 2.8 3.0 1.0 0.4 9.8 ARS St Albans 4.0 2.4 0.6 1.4 12.8 AWS Uitenhage 11.8 9.4 NIL 0.4 0.8 MAN Woodridge 11.0 9.3 0.2 1.4 2.0 Catchment areas      AWS Joubertina 1.6 4.8 4.4 1.2 4.0 ARS Kareedouw 7.0 3.2 4.0 0.8 12.8 Man Kareedouw 7.0 2.0 3.5 1.0 10.0 Man Kouga Dam 9.0 16.5 0.3 0.5 * AWS Patensie 25.0 12.8 NIL 0.2 4.2 Man       Other Towns      AWS Addo 26.4 3.0 NIL NIL NIL AWS Bisho/KWT 11.0 10.8 2.0 NIL NIL AWS Cape St Francis NIL * 0.2 NIL 5.2 AWS Cradock 21.4 0.4 NIL NIL NIL AWS East London 2.2 9.2 2.8 1.0 7.0 AWS Fort Beaufort * 5.0 0.2 NIL NIL AWS George 33.0 30.6 9.5 0.3 2.1 AWS Graaff Reinet 6.6 1.6 0.8 NIL NIL AWS Grahamstown 16.4 5.2 3.0 NIL NIL AWS Henry`s Flats 13.2 3.0 0.2 NIL NIL AWS Joubertina 1.6 4.8 4.4 1.2 4.0 AWS Mossel Bay 16.6 12.8 16.6 3.4 7.2 AWS Mthatha 0.4 8.8 1.8 1.0 1.0 AWS Plettenberg Bay 17.2 22.2 10.6 4.8 7.8 AWS Port Alfred 6.0 0.6 0.4 NIL 1.8 AWS Queenstown 1.8 5.2 0.8 0.8 1.8 * no contact 0.0 = Drops  Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Barga